05/01/15

Introduction

  • Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) Consumer Complaint Database
    • Number of complaints: 377850
    • Number of variables: 14
    • Number of companies: 2850
    • Number of unique complaint issues: 96
    • Date range: 2011-12-01 to 2015-04-28
    • Data retrieved from Data.gov
  • Topics covered in this presentation
    • Data cleaning
    • Visualization of state-level statistics via chroopleths
    • Plotting zipcode-level statistics using the ggmap package

Data Cleaning

  • Transform the variable names to lower case
  • Remove '.' from variable names
  • Exclude data from U.S. territories
  • Apply a maximum percent missing threshold to remove partial observations
  • Remove whitespace from the company type
  • For each database variable:
    • Transform to lower case
    • Remove apostrophe (e.g. change cont'd to contd)
    • Remove punctuation
    • Replace multiple spaces with a single space

Data Cleaning (cont.)

  • Remove white space from the company type
  • Aggregate the complaint issues into 12 categories
  • Remove the "other" category
  • Append city, state, latitude, & longitude from the zipcode R package
  • Add a companyid variable
  • Convert date variables
  • Convert factor variables
  • Percentage of data removed during data cleaning: 11.4%
